mutation(
    $project: ID!
    $item: ID!
    $status_field: ID!
    $status_value: String!
  )  {
  updateProjectV2ItemFieldValue(
    input: {
     projectId: $project
      itemId: $item
      fieldId: $status_field
      value: { 
        singleSelectOptionId: $status_value
        }
    }
  ) {
    projectV2Item {
      id
    }
  }
}' -f project=${{ secrets.PROJECT_PLANNING_ID }} -f item=${{ steps.add_project.outputs.itemId }} -f status_field=${{ secrets.PLANNING_TEAM_FIELD_ID }} -f status_value=ed46988b --silent`.

Generate a GitHub Workflow named `cla` for a GitHub repository whose primary programming language is C++. This workflow will be triggered by multiple events: 1) a comment on an issue or pull request is created. 2) a pull request is created, a pull request is closed or a pull request's head branch is updated. The workflow has one job. The job id of the 1st job is `cla`. This job will run on ubuntu-latest runner. The job `cla` has 2 steps. The 1st step is named `Get Team Members` and its id is `team`. This step runs action `actions/github-script` whose commit is 7a5c598405937d486b0331594b5da2b14db670da. The step defines 3 input parameters for the action: `github-token` is set to `${{ secrets.PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN }}`, `result-encoding` is set to `string` and `script` is set to `const members = await github.paginate(
  github.rest.orgs.listMembers,
  { org: "skalenetwork" },
);
return members.map(m => m.login).join(",");
`. The 2nd step is named `CLA Assistant`. This step will run only if the condition((github.event.comment.body == 'recheck' || github.event.comment.body == 'I have read the CLA Document and I hereby sign the CLA') || github.event_name == 'pull_request_target') is met. The step sets 2 environment variables to use: `GITHUB_TOKEN` is set to `${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}` and `PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN` is set to `${{ secrets.PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN }}`. This step runs action `cla-assistant/github-action` whose commit is ba066dbae3769e2ce93ec8cfc4fdc51b9db628ba. The step defines 5 input parameters for the action: `path-to-signatures` is set to `signatures/version1/cla.json`, `path-to-document` is set to `https://skale.network/cla.txt`, `remote-organization-name` is set to `skalenetwork`, `remote-repository-name` is set to `cla-sigs` and `allowlist` is set to `${{ steps.team.outputs.result }},*[bot]`.

Generate a GitHub Workflow named `Tag` for a GitHub repository whose primary programming language is TypeScript. This workflow will be triggered by an event: someone manually triggers the workflow. This workflow receives 2 inputs: version-this input represents version and it must be supplied; tag-this input represents tag, its default value is latest and it must be supplied. The workflow modifies the default permissions for the GITHUB_TOKEN: the workflow disables permissions for the GITHUB_TOKEN across all scopes. This permission setting applies to all jobs in the workflow. The workflow has one job. The 1st job is named `Tagging ${{ github.event.inputs.version }} as ${{ github.event.inputs.tag }}` and its job id is `build`. This job will run on ubuntu-latest runner. This job references release environment. The job `build` has 2 steps. The 1st step is named `Setup Node`. This step runs action `actions/setup-node` tagged as v3. The 2nd step is named `Update tag`. The step sets an environment variable to use: `npm_config_//registry.npmjs.org/:_authToken` is set to `${{ secrets.NPM_TOKEN }}`. This step runs a script: `npm dist-tag add pnpm@${{ github.event.inputs.version }} ${{ github.event.inputs.tag }}
npm dist-tag add @pnpm/exe@${{ github.event.inputs.version }} ${{ github.event.inputs.tag }}
`.

Generate a GitHub Workflow named `nf-core AWS test` for a GitHub repository whose primary programming language is Nextflow. This workflow will be triggered by an event: someone manually triggers the workflow. The workflow has one job. The 1st job is named `Run AWS tests` and its job id is `run-tower`. This job will run only if the condition(github.repository == 'nf-core/mag') is met. This job will run on ubuntu-latest runner. The job `run-tower` has one step. The 1st step is named `Launch workflow via tower`. This step runs action `nf-core/tower-action` tagged as v3. The step defines 6 input parameters for the action: `workspace_id` is set to `${{ secrets.TOWER_WORKSPACE_ID }}`, `access_token` is set to `${{ secrets.TOWER_ACCESS_TOKEN }}`, `compute_env` is set to `${{ secrets.TOWER_COMPUTE_ENV }}`, `workdir` is set to `s3://${{ secrets.AWS_S3_BUCKET }}/work/mag/work-${{ github.sha }}`, `parameters` is set to `{
  "outdir": "s3://${{ secrets.AWS_S3_BUCKET }}/mag/results-test-${{ github.sha }}"
}
` and `profiles` is set to `test,aws_tower`.
